"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-12-Prejudice-Double-standards-Americans-on-Olympic-doping-controversy-1w0nH9LWHT2-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Global Stringer  Copied  The U.S. has accused Chinese swimmers at the 2024 Paris Olympics of doping, despite heavy testing for athletes of Team China returning negative results.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 251, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9141775782880168, \"rank\": 0.08703503570473343, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999994140218302, \"rank\": 5.85977873084257e-07, \"text\": \"Team China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics called it the \\\"most intensive testing\\\" before the Games, with an average of 21 tests for each Chinese swimmer since the start of the year, compared with 3.4 tests for all swimmers in the same period.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9141775782880168, \"rank\": 0.08703503570473343, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The doping claims quickly prompted fevered discussions.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Up to 90 percent of U.S. athletes are not competing under the world anti-doping code,\\\" World Anti-Doping Agency President Witold Banka has said.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"score\": 0.9999981169286907, \"rank\": 1.8830746584184754e-06, \"text\": \"Witold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanhua_District\", \"score\": 0.7022361944079623, \"rank\": 0.3334297300291095, \"text\": \"Banka\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanhua_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanhua_District\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, the Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act\\u00a0extends U.S. law enforcement jurisdiction to international sporting competitions involving American athletes or those with financial connections to the U.S.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8567268417772855, \"rank\": 0.1670748723734221, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999989632081824, \"rank\": 9.879269274391428e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The act claims to be aimed at combating doping, but American professional and college athletes are exempt from the legislation.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1054, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999989632081824, \"rank\": 9.879269274391428e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CGTN took to the streets of New York to ask Americans about their views on the controversy.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999991645187345, \"rank\": 4.1851087415948333e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Retiree Peter Lowes said doping should be completely banned, prejudice should be eliminated, and the Olympics have to be a fair playing field.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Peter\", \"score\": 0.8813455551914471, \"rank\": 0.09915934999644985, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Peter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Peter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": []}]}"